Compiler pipeline from steno-theory source (`.steno` files) to Plover JSON dictionaries, LSP snippets, and structural blocks. The pipeline chains four one-way passes: parse (fenced text to AST), expand (count fan-out, type-append chains, variants), and render (Plover dicts for plain and smart editor profiles, LSP snippets, `@literal` blocks).

Data flows strictly forward through the pipeline; every error is a typed error carrying 1-based source line. The library exports the full pipeline and intermediate types for consumption by binaries (`build-dict`, `build-nvim`, `measure`, `viz-data`), which alone perform file I/O — library code never writes output.